OD^2 &= d^2 + e^2 + (f - r)^2.
\end{align*}Hence,
\begin{align*}
(d - p)^2 + e^2 + f^2 &= d^2 + (e - q)^2 + f^2, \\
(d - p)^2 + e^2 + f^2 &= d^2 + e^2 + (f - r)^2.
\end{align*}Subtracting these equations, we get
\[(e - q)^2 - (f - r)^2 = 0.\]Hence, $e - q = f - r,$ so $q - r = e - f.$

