Let $r$ be the radius of the sphere.  Then $OA = OB = OC = r.$  Let $E$ be the foot of the perpendicular from $O$ to plane $ABC.$  Then $OE = r.$  Let $M$ be the midpoint of $\overline{BC}.$  Then $OM = \frac{r}{\cos \angle AOM}.$  But
